MUFJ Securities Names Toyoizumi President Replacing Akikusa

-- B y   T a k a h i k o   H y u g a
-- 
2011-04-28T08:17:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/mufj-securities-names-toyoizumi-president-replacing-akikusa-1-.html
Mitsubishi UFJ Securities Holdings
Co., a brokerage unit of  Japan ’s biggest publicly traded bank,
named Toshiro Toyoizumi as president to replace Fumiyuki Akikusa.  Toyoizumi was also appointed head of Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan
Stanley Securities Co., a joint venture with the New York-based
lender, Mitsubishi UFJ said in a statement in Tokyo today.  Toyoizumi, 61, joined the bank’s predecessor after
graduating from Keio University in 1973.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takahiko Hyuga in Tokyo at 
 thyuga@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Russell Ward at 
 rward16@bloomberg.net  